title: Evidence Custodian
name: Tom Prevette
description: Oversees and Manages the operational aspects of ongoing projects and serves as liaison between project management and planning, project team, and line management. Reviews status of projects and budgets; manages schedules and prepares status reports. Assesses project issues and develops resolutions to meet productivity, quality, and client-satisfaction goals and objectives. Develops mechanisms for monitoring project progress and for intervention and problem solving with project managers, line managers, and clients. Under direction of the Department of Defense, maintain all evidence and property in the custody of the Defense Computer Forensics Laboratory. Support all sections within the Defense Cyber Crime Center (DC3) with evidence retention, packaging, control, inventory, and data entry ensuring all items are stored in accordance with standards set forth by American Society of Crime Laboratory Directors (ASCLAD) and DC3 policy. Maintain security and chain of custody for all evidence and property including written and computer database records of items. Tasks include inventory, data entry, storage of items/evidence and safekeeping items. Ensure that items received into Evidence are in the proper packaging for evidentiary items (i.e. antistatic bags, etc.), sealed, and marked to maintain evidence integrity and prevent deleterious change, theft, loss, contamination and cross contamination. Set up appointments with outside agencies to coordinate release of evidence upon completion/closure of examination when authorized. Ability to complete repetitive work while being extremely detail oriented exhibiting a high degree of integrity and the ability to organize, alphabetize and arrange property and paperwork in sequential order. Lifting and movement of large and/or heavy items at times.

description: Worked as part of a team providing flight support; interpretation of surveillance systems products; O&M on Aerostat avionics, acoustic sensors, ground sensors; operation of EO/IR sensor payloads, radar systems, military and telemetry radios. Conducted preventive maintenance, troubleshooting, and repair of mechanical equipment; as well as O&M of Aerostats and mooring systems in support of the Persistent Threat Detection System (PTDS) program. Completed a 30-month assignment located within Eastern Paktika in Afghanistan. Was required to travel within the country and perform duties while living in this austere environment. Performed O&M of mechanical equipment to include one or more of the following: high lift vehicles, forklifts, hydraulic systems, winch systems, tether/cable handling systems, industrial generator sets, power switch gear, HVAC, and cranes. Performed O&M of electro-mechanical equipment to include one or more of the following: hydraulic/servo valves, hydraulic actuators, control systems, and test and diagnostic equipment. Experience in reading and interpret engineering drawings/blueprints; Proficient in computer/software operations, MS Office and Windows OS. Passed a pre-employment physical exam, dental exam, and drug screen. Experience with Aerostat or Lighter-than-Air (LTA) systems; Maintenance of electromechanical control systems; O&M of C4ISR systems. Experience with reading electronic schematics, compressed gas systems, and AC/DC electrical systems. Experience with lead soldering and fiber splicing, networking & information systems and EO/IR sensor payload operations. Experience with military operations, acronyms, and military chain of command having effective success using oral and written communication skills. Logistic Manager -PTDS Program Regional Command - East Afghanistan - Assigned at a GS12 equivalent position, Attend Daily Brigade Meetings to plan and provide support for Mission Critical movements.
